{"id":417780561,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 10 months","timestamp":1604770287,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"76 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/417780561/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers II","memory":"14.2 MB","code":"# Definition for singly-linked list.\n# class ListNode:\n#     def __init__(self, val=0, next=None):\n#         self.val = val\n#         self.next = next\nclass Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        s1, s2 = [], []\n        head1, head2 = l1, l2\n        while head1:\n            s1.append(head1.val)\n            head1 = head1.next\n        while head2:\n            s2.append(head2.val)\n            head2 = head2.next\n        \n        head, carry = None, 0\n        while s1 or s2:\n            x1 = s1.pop() if s1 else 0\n            x2 = s2.pop() if s2 else 0\n            summ = (x1 + x2 + carry) % 10\n            carry = (x1 + x2 + carry) // 10\n            node = ListNode(summ)\n            node.next = head\n            head = node\n            \n        if carry:\n            node = ListNode(carry)\n            node.next = head\n            head = node\n            \n        return head","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
